# LapyTrack — Frontend

## Key files
- `src/App.js` — routes; `/job/:id` is public job sheet (no auth)
- `src/lib/api.js` — axios instance, `API`, `publicFileUrl(path)` for job sheet photos
- `src/contexts/AuthContext.jsx` — PIN lock, setup, email login
- `src/pages/PinAuth.jsx` — setup (shop + email + password + PIN) and login
- `src/pages/PublicJobCard.jsx` — printable job sheet; use `publicFileUrl` for photos
- `src/pages/DeviceDetail.jsx` — `PhotoImg` fetches `/api/files/` with auth token
- `vercel.json` — `yarn install`, `yarn build`, output `build/`

## API client
```javascript
import { api, API, publicFileUrl } from "@/lib/api";
// Authenticated: api.get("/devices")
// Public job photos: publicFileUrl("uploads/abc.png")
```
- `withCredentials: true`, 15s timeout
- Bearer token from `localStorage.access_token` (fallback to cookie)

## React Query
- Configured in `src/index.js`: `staleTime: 120_000`, use for dashboard/devices caching
- Prefer `useQuery` over raw `useEffect` fetch for list pages

## UI
- Shadcn components in `src/components/ui/`
- Branding: "KRISH COMPUTER" / "LapyTrack" / `lapytrack-logo.svg`
- Mobile: bottom tab bar in `Layout.jsx`; desktop sidebar

## Do not
- Use `react-scripts build` directly — use `yarn build` (Craco)
- Hardcode backend URL — always `process.env.REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL`
- Point QR/job URLs at `localhost` in production builds
